979
01:12:23.890 --> 01:12:24.400
Audio shared by David S. Kong: But you…

980
01:12:24.400 --> 01:12:27.669
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You see him scan over the crowd.

981
01:12:28.080 --> 01:12:33.400
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You see his eyes fall away down the slope of the hills, to where the…

982
01:12:33.680 --> 01:12:37.349
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): People are climbing into the rowboat to head onwards.

983
01:12:37.540 --> 01:12:52.969
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You see him note sharp voices raised among a small, cluster of people off and away below the, below the patios. And then you see him look directly at the owl and make eye contact

984
01:12:54.000 --> 01:12:57.390
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Nod to himself, and step back inside the house.

985
01:13:01.110 --> 01:13:02.930
Audio shared by David S. Kong: The guards raise a hand in greeting.

986
01:13:04.470 --> 01:13:13.729
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): But then a look of confusion comes over their face. They're two deeply, deeply wrinkled, sort of elderly men.

987
01:13:14.530 --> 01:13:16.030
Audio shared by David S. Kong: pot-bellied…

988
01:13:16.030 --> 01:13:22.399
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): With, you know, the sort of hoods that someone wears that's just, like, the separate hood from the cloak

989
01:13:24.750 --> 01:13:26.710
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And they… they look at you.

990
01:13:27.070 --> 01:13:28.840
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): With a note of confusion, and then…

991
01:13:28.840 --> 01:13:36.420
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And then lift their noses to sniff, and sniff almost dog-like, and in their sniffing,

992
01:13:38.140 --> 01:13:41.270
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): There's a strange moment of not understanding if you're seeing.

993
01:13:41.270 --> 01:13:46.150
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Men pretending to be dogs, or dogs pretending to be men.

994
01:13:46.680 --> 01:13:49.489
Audio shared by David S. Kong: But they finished that, and then.

995
01:13:50.260 --> 01:13:55.109
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Not a greeting, and say… Well met and welcome, mortals.

996
01:13:56.200 --> 01:13:57.200
David S. Kong: What?

997
01:13:57.640 --> 01:13:58.120
Kate Sackton: Word dope.

998
01:13:58.120 --> 01:13:59.789
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Well met and welcome.

999
01:13:59.790 --> 01:14:00.550
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Mortals.

1000
01:14:03.490 --> 01:14:08.560
David S. Kong: Kaito gives a flourish of his cape, What?

1001
01:14:08.560 --> 01:14:10.010
Tim Sackton: Language do they say this in?

1002
01:14:12.760 --> 01:14:13.710
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Amen.

1003
01:14:14.570 --> 01:14:16.190
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Heavily accented comments.

1004
01:14:16.840 --> 01:14:17.779
David S. Kong: Accented ham?

1005
01:14:19.880 --> 01:14:22.210
Audio shared by David S. Kong: ambiguously.

1006
01:14:22.720 --> 01:14:23.660
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Goodbye.

1007
01:14:26.390 --> 01:14:27.200
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Yeah.

1008
01:14:27.530 --> 01:14:30.240
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Kate is a flourish. Greetings.

1009
01:14:31.890 --> 01:14:38.390
David S. Kong: But before he walks in, though, he's, he glances and says, The festivities ending soon?

1010
01:14:41.100 --> 01:14:42.300
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Indeed.

1011
01:14:42.430 --> 01:14:43.180
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Indeed.

1012
01:14:43.630 --> 01:14:45.390
Audio shared by David S. Kong: The party is ending.

1013
01:14:45.430 --> 01:14:46.570
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You're just in time.

1014
01:14:49.720 --> 01:14:50.140
David S. Kong: 4.

1015
01:14:52.190 --> 01:14:55.640
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The party before it ends, says one, with a chuckle.

1016
01:14:57.140 --> 01:14:57.990
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Indeed.

1017
01:14:58.270 --> 01:14:59.370
Audio shared by David S. Kong: My favorite time.

1018
01:14:59.810 --> 01:15:01.470
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Yeah, he gets ahold of that.

1019
01:15:06.120 --> 01:15:08.369
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Where have you… come from?

1020
01:15:08.500 --> 01:15:09.910
Audio shared by David S. Kong: It's unusual.

1021
01:15:09.910 --> 01:15:12.929
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): To see so many of you together at once at this time of night.

1022
01:15:15.310 --> 01:15:17.250
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Damn.

1023
01:15:17.250 --> 01:15:19.009
David S. Kong: Do we use detectas now?

1024
01:15:19.590 --> 01:15:20.969
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Find out in a minute.

1025
01:15:21.990 --> 01:15:23.459
Audio shared by David S. Kong: No. Not now.

1026
01:15:26.480 --> 01:15:27.789
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Where did we come from?

1027
01:15:28.810 --> 01:15:29.939
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Down the road, of course.

1028
01:15:32.270 --> 01:15:38.900
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The one who hasn't said anything so far chuckles, like you've made a very incisive joke.

1029
01:15:43.660 --> 01:15:46.430
David S. Kong: And may I ask, can you share more about the party?

1030
01:15:47.290 --> 01:15:48.569
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Well, our apologies for being late.

1031
01:15:51.440 --> 01:15:53.820
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Yeah, I…

1032
01:15:54.520 --> 01:15:55.930
Audio shared by David S. Kong: I'll tell you this.

1033
01:15:56.250 --> 01:15:58.009
Audio shared by David S. Kong: We belong to the road.

1034
01:15:58.380 --> 01:15:59.650
Audio shared by David S. Kong: to the party.

1035
01:16:00.090 --> 01:16:08.979
Audio shared by David S. Kong: The party isn't our story. We know what we hear and smell and see through the gate, but this is as far as we go.

1036
01:16:10.650 --> 01:16:12.990
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Well… Perhaps some candor.

1037
01:16:13.870 --> 01:16:18.230
Audio shared by David S. Kong: We came from the road. We saw bodies.

1038
01:16:19.530 --> 01:16:21.079
David S. Kong: Presumably coming from here.

1039
01:16:21.300 --> 01:16:22.619
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Maybe, maybe not.

1040
01:16:23.880 --> 01:16:29.069
Audio shared by David S. Kong: I love a good party. Gives another flourish and a wink.

1041
01:16:29.340 --> 01:16:32.240
Audio shared by David S. Kong: But also, the bodies.

1042
01:16:33.080 --> 01:16:37.220
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Anything you might be able to share about the party?

1043
01:16:37.220 --> 01:16:38.010
David S. Kong: And the Lord here?

1044
01:16:42.590 --> 01:16:45.900
Audio shared by David S. Kong: The ones you passed did not come from this house.

1045
01:16:46.220 --> 01:16:47.839
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): But further up the road.

1046
01:16:52.680 --> 01:16:54.490
Mike: Is there anything further up the road?

1047
01:16:56.100 --> 01:16:57.450
Mike: I mean, the road keeps going, right?

1048
01:16:59.200 --> 01:17:02.430
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Yep, yeah, the road absolutely keeps going.

1049
01:17:05.580 --> 01:17:11.310
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The road… the road goes on and on and on.

1050
01:17:11.730 --> 01:17:14.470
Audio shared by David S. Kong: I'm gonna have to pull up the right…

1051
01:17:14.470 --> 01:17:15.150
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Notes.

1052
01:17:23.480 --> 01:17:31.189
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): In the Twilight Kingdom, there are a dozen dozen houses, homes, and holes, with the setting sun just over the horizon.

1053
01:17:33.770 --> 01:17:34.809
David S. Kong: This is the Twilight Kingdom.

1054
01:17:37.270 --> 01:17:38.600
Mike: Which.

1055
01:17:41.510 --> 01:17:43.059
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Which way is the road going?

1056
01:17:44.340 --> 01:17:45.250
Audio shared by David S. Kong: towards the sun?

1057
01:17:45.950 --> 01:17:47.640
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Away from…

1058
01:17:47.640 --> 01:17:54.390
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The road goes almost, as near as you can tell, the road goes parallel…

1059
01:17:54.680 --> 01:17:58.159
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): To what in any other place would be the north-south axis.

1060
01:17:58.350 --> 01:18:01.529
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Exactly between day and night.

1061
01:18:03.020 --> 01:18:09.179
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And you notice, in fact, having been here for at least an hour now, that the sun has not moved in the sky.

1062
01:18:19.770 --> 01:18:21.140
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Do you have…

1063
01:18:21.470 --> 01:18:27.110
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Sensing your confusion, the same guard says, do you have where you're from.

1064
01:18:28.970 --> 01:18:32.910
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Disease that spreads from one… person to another.

1065
01:18:36.120 --> 01:18:36.720
Kate Sackton: Yes.

1066
01:18:37.910 --> 01:18:39.559
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Well, we don't have that here.

1067
01:18:41.000 --> 01:18:42.369
Audio shared by David S. Kong: But we have something…

1068
01:18:42.520 --> 01:18:48.389
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Similar, something, mmm…

1069
01:18:50.260 --> 01:18:53.040
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Sometimes people get infected in a way…

1070
01:18:54.010 --> 01:18:57.219
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Sometimes people get caught by a bad smell.

1071
01:18:58.450 --> 01:19:06.200
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And that smell… Can cause disaster and spread to more people with the bad smell.

1072
01:19:09.160 --> 01:19:10.800
Audio shared by David S. Kong: We belong to the road.

1073
01:19:11.240 --> 01:19:13.650
Audio shared by David S. Kong: We keep the road safe.

1074
01:19:15.360 --> 01:19:18.229
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Sometimes, the people with the bad smell

1075
01:19:18.450 --> 01:19:21.859
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You can't get the bad smell out of them any other way.

1076
01:19:23.730 --> 01:19:25.059
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I think that's what you saw.

1077
01:19:32.500 --> 01:19:35.439
Mike: They only have spears, they don't have any bows or anything like that.

1078
01:19:39.930 --> 01:19:44.440
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Though their feet are shod in plain, soft boots.

1079
01:19:47.750 --> 01:19:52.499
David S. Kong: So… The bodies… you guys don't have anything to do with the bodies.

1080
01:19:56.940 --> 01:20:01.639
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): My people do, some of us stay at the gate, some of us travel the road.

1081
01:20:02.460 --> 01:20:04.130
David S. Kong: But you don't know what to do with the bodies.

1082
01:20:05.640 --> 01:20:07.259
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The two of us? No. No, no.

1083
01:20:07.920 --> 01:20:09.240
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Our place is the gate.

1084
01:20:09.900 --> 01:20:14.400
David S. Kong: Right. And, and again, the Lord of the manor here?

1085
01:20:16.510 --> 01:20:17.500
David S. Kong: What do you know of him?

1086
01:20:28.590 --> 01:20:30.749
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): He came to the gate once.

1087
01:20:34.110 --> 01:20:36.020
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): He came to the gate once.

1088
01:20:39.100 --> 01:20:46.419
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Just at the height of the party, Just before… You know what it's like?

1089
01:20:46.760 --> 01:20:54.380
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): When a gathering starts to come apart, you can feel it before anyone's even left. He came in that moment.

1090
01:20:58.660 --> 01:20:59.930
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): To tell us to…

1091
01:21:02.520 --> 01:21:03.040
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Be careful.

1092
01:21:03.040 --> 01:21:04.739
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Careful of travelers on the road.

1093
01:21:05.590 --> 01:21:08.090
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): To smell very carefully for the bad smell.

1094
01:21:09.160 --> 01:21:12.829
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): But to let in any mortal who wanted entrance.

1095
01:21:14.160 --> 01:21:16.779
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): It was a strange thing, I remember it, too.

1096
01:21:17.130 --> 01:21:23.880
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I would have thought he just said any guest who wanted entrance, but he said any mortal who wants entrance, send them in.

1097
01:21:29.830 --> 01:21:30.230
Kate Sackton: Excellent.

1098
01:21:30.230 --> 01:21:32.060
David S. Kong: When was this directive?

1099
01:21:34.780 --> 01:21:41.339
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Just, just, just as the party began to end. Just after the height of it.

1100
01:21:41.870 --> 01:21:44.029
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): We arrived, of course, when it was just beginning.

1101
01:21:44.980 --> 01:21:47.260
David S. Kong: Oh, so very… quite recently. How long has this party been going?

1102
01:21:51.310 --> 01:21:53.250
Audio shared by David S. Kong: He shakes his head, confused.

1103
01:21:54.310 --> 01:21:59.249
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Like you're asking a sort of a ridiculous question.

1104
01:22:00.790 --> 01:22:04.690
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): began it… Breached its peak, and now it's coming apart.

1105
01:22:05.010 --> 01:22:06.910
David S. Kong: Yeah, yeah, yeah, no, I understand.

1106
01:22:08.200 --> 01:22:11.480
Audio shared by David S. Kong: You mentioned, the other…

1107
01:22:11.480 --> 01:22:12.779
David S. Kong: Lord's down the road.

1108
01:22:13.200 --> 01:22:15.090
David S. Kong: Pensions?

1109
01:22:16.480 --> 01:22:17.230
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Wait, say that again?

1110
01:22:17.730 --> 01:22:18.650
David S. Kong: Tensions?

1111
01:22:19.490 --> 01:22:20.510
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Of… sorry.

1112
01:22:20.930 --> 01:22:25.060
David S. Kong: Well, you just said the bodies, they're not from here, they're not from this house, the bodies are from another house.

1113
01:22:25.160 --> 01:22:26.870
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Do you know what house they're from?

1114
01:22:29.730 --> 01:22:30.930
Audio shared by David S. Kong: There's a house…

1115
01:22:31.100 --> 01:22:35.579
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): That when people come out of, they come out of it with the bad smell sometimes.

1116
01:22:36.240 --> 01:22:36.920
Audio shared by David S. Kong: What?

1117
01:22:37.260 --> 01:22:38.319
Mike: What does that smell like?

1118
01:22:41.000 --> 01:22:42.510
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Just…

1119
01:22:42.510 --> 01:22:43.680
Mike: So we can avoid it.

1120
01:22:48.430 --> 01:22:54.909
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): He looks thoughtful and deep for a sec, and then locks in eye contact with you and says.

1121
01:22:55.920 --> 01:23:01.500
Audio shared by David S. Kong: It smells exactly unlike anything else I have ever smelled in my entire living.

1122
01:23:04.670 --> 01:23:06.469
Audio shared by David S. Kong: It's the opposite of smell.

1123
01:23:11.010 --> 01:23:11.840
Mike: what's confused.

1124
01:23:18.390 --> 01:23:18.900
Mike: Thank you.

1125
01:23:18.900 --> 01:23:19.730
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): gives a nun.

1126
01:23:22.760 --> 01:23:24.939
Tim Sackton: Are there other mortals with this party?

1127
01:23:26.680 --> 01:23:31.029
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): There's a handful, a few have come by boat.

1128
01:23:33.280 --> 01:23:36.070
Audio shared by David S. Kong: The halflings came soon after it began.

1129
01:23:36.240 --> 01:23:37.830
Audio shared by David S. Kong: They always seem to.

1130
01:23:38.840 --> 01:23:40.070
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Thanks.

1131
01:23:40.220 --> 01:23:44.409
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I think there was a dwarf… he turns to the other one, the dwarf went in, did they come out?

1132
01:23:48.640 --> 01:23:52.000
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And a few I couldn't quite tell. None of them had the bad smell, though.

1133
01:23:55.390 --> 01:23:56.479
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Did one…

1134
01:23:57.670 --> 01:23:58.509
Mike: Come and go.

1135
01:24:02.920 --> 01:24:03.389
Audio shared by David S. Kong: I…

1136
01:24:04.650 --> 01:24:06.179
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Any number of them have come and gone.

1137
01:24:09.940 --> 01:24:11.599
Mike: Since the party began to end?

1138
01:24:14.840 --> 01:24:18.099
Audio shared by David S. Kong: He looks thoughtful for a moment, as though just sort of,

1139
01:24:18.100 --> 01:24:20.420
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Trying to put that together for the first time.

1140
01:24:21.740 --> 01:24:23.129
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Let's see…

1141
01:24:30.530 --> 01:24:37.930
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Yeah… they… Yes. They've been going more than coming lately, I suppose.

1142
01:24:39.540 --> 01:24:41.040
Mike: That is what ending means, right?

1143
01:24:51.340 --> 01:24:52.630
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Would you like to go in?

1144
01:24:54.710 --> 01:24:57.700
Mike: The house down at the end of the road, the one that's kind of fallen apart.

1145
01:24:59.860 --> 01:25:00.510
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Heat.

1146
01:25:03.130 --> 01:25:07.799
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Says in a language you don't recognize what surely must be some curse and spits.

1147
01:25:10.770 --> 01:25:12.749
Audio shared by David S. Kong: It's a bad-smelling place. We don't go there.

1148
01:25:15.470 --> 01:25:17.740
Tim Sackton: Does the road end in the other direction, too?

1149
01:25:22.020 --> 01:25:24.620
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Roads don't end.

1150
01:25:25.530 --> 01:25:29.149
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): They only ever go… On and on.

1151
01:25:33.000 --> 01:25:35.060
Mike: No, some roads don't…

1152
01:25:35.780 --> 01:25:40.300
Mike: Edric, like, covers up his mouth, like, I probably should get in an argument with them and stop stalking.

1153
01:25:41.100 --> 01:25:43.800
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): We belong to the road, he says. We know.

1154
01:25:45.630 --> 01:25:47.640
Tim Sackton: Should we go in?

1155
01:25:48.870 --> 01:25:56.290
Tim Sackton: Char says to everybody else, in… Poles, not common.

1156
01:25:59.020 --> 01:26:01.340
Tim Sackton: Which I presume everybody understands.

1157
01:26:03.790 --> 01:26:05.570
David S. Kong: Let's do it.

1158
01:26:06.780 --> 01:26:08.240
Tim Sackton: We would like to enter.

1159
01:26:09.440 --> 01:26:10.270
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Very good.

1160
01:26:11.670 --> 01:26:12.920
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Did you bring gifts?

1161
01:26:14.230 --> 01:26:19.799
David S. Kong: You know, I literally was gonna say that at the very beginning, that, unfortunately.

1162
01:26:20.210 --> 01:26:22.369
David S. Kong: Well, I'll put it this way.

1163
01:26:23.190 --> 01:26:26.880
David S. Kong: We may have… gifts are a relative term.

1164
01:26:27.450 --> 01:26:35.689
David S. Kong: In the sense that, something that I possess may be a gift to some, it may not be to others.

1165
01:26:35.820 --> 01:26:43.759
David S. Kong: So, we come bearing our possessions. To the extent that some of those may be worthy and deemed gifts.

1166
01:26:45.020 --> 01:26:46.279
David S. Kong: Then we have them.

1167
01:26:47.550 --> 01:26:48.950
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You won't like that.

1168
01:26:49.060 --> 01:26:49.660
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You won'.

1169
01:26:49.660 --> 01:26:50.150
David S. Kong: like that.

1170
01:26:51.340 --> 01:26:54.659
David S. Kong: Collectively, do we have any, any things? Anything nice?

1171
01:26:54.760 --> 01:26:58.039
David S. Kong: Classic, classic things that might… one might think as a gift.

1172
01:27:01.390 --> 01:27:06.439
Mike: I, I've… Some water blasted by the Night Queen.

1173
01:27:10.570 --> 01:27:11.890
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Let's do this.

1174
01:27:11.890 --> 01:27:13.629
Tim Sackton: Song of a Loon?

1175
01:27:14.410 --> 01:27:16.649
Tim Sackton: Have you heard a loon call before?

1176
01:27:18.810 --> 01:27:19.610
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): No.

1177
01:27:21.010 --> 01:27:21.880
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): What is that?

1178
01:27:24.020 --> 01:27:25.969
Tim Sackton: gift for the Lord of the Manor.

1179
01:27:26.720 --> 01:27:27.350
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Very good.

1180
01:27:27.350 --> 01:27:30.930
Tim Sackton: Would he approve of me sharing my gifts with you?

1181
01:27:39.320 --> 01:27:40.050
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Listen.

1182
01:27:40.450 --> 01:27:41.910
Audio shared by David S. Kong: I am bribable.

1183
01:27:41.910 --> 01:27:47.360
