1329
01:37:05.850 --> 01:37:08.850
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Well, you know, my kinds.

1330
01:37:09.600 --> 01:37:11.439
Audio shared by David S. Kong: We accidentally have one dream.

1331
01:37:12.300 --> 01:37:21.460
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And it only happens once, so… I actually share your nostalgia. Well, I guess you're… for you, it's a curiosity, since you've never had a dream, right? Isn't that correct?

1332
01:37:21.460 --> 01:37:21.870
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): -

1333
01:37:21.870 --> 01:37:28.000
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Yeah, I, I, I empathize with that,

1334
01:37:30.090 --> 01:37:32.840
Audio shared by David S. Kong: But for me, it's more nostalgia, because I've only ever had.

1335
01:37:33.320 --> 01:37:33.990
David S. Kong: Wondering.

1336
01:37:36.330 --> 01:37:38.680
David S. Kong: But if you like, I can share you some snippets of that dream.

1337
01:37:39.610 --> 01:37:40.000
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Tell me.

1338
01:37:40.720 --> 01:37:42.100
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Well…

1339
01:37:42.100 --> 01:37:46.140
David S. Kong: Well, it was the one dream, and it was a long dream.

1340
01:37:46.470 --> 01:37:50.690
David S. Kong: there were parts of the dream, the parts that I'm nostalgic for the most,

1341
01:37:51.630 --> 01:38:08.470
David S. Kong: It's less one moment or one narrative and more just a whole bunch of scenes clipped and chopped and strewn together, almost like a patchwork of a quilt that, you know, is made of so many different colors and shapes and textures and smells.

1342
01:38:09.820 --> 01:38:11.070
Audio shared by David S. Kong: But it would go from…

1343
01:38:11.070 --> 01:38:19.600
David S. Kong: One scene with just massive trees of unimaginable size, swaying in huge roots and just…

1344
01:38:19.840 --> 01:38:25.799
David S. Kong: Large, craggy grass, and this kind of feeling of something so raw and alive.

1345
01:38:25.800 --> 01:38:27.030
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And then all of a sudden.

1346
01:38:27.170 --> 01:38:31.470
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Nothingness in the night sky, and just… Black.

1347
01:38:31.560 --> 01:38:35.839
David S. Kong: Except stars. Everywhere. And then shifting from stars to blackness.

1348
01:38:36.240 --> 01:38:59.060
David S. Kong: And then all of a sudden, the crashing of waves smashing over your head, and you're in a boat rocking up and down, and up and down, and your body's swaying back and forth, and then you feel like you're in the middle of the ocean, except you're not. You're in the middle of a fire, and you're in a flame inside of the fireplace, and it's just raging hot, and you're sweating, and it's just so incredibly uncomfortable, until you hear the sound of a voice singing.

1349
01:38:59.150 --> 01:39:11.470
David S. Kong: But it's your siblings, except do you have siblings or not have siblings in real life? It's hard to say, but the voices are so golden and beautiful and piercing, and they pull you out of the fire, and the next thing you know, you look down, and

1350
01:39:11.470 --> 01:39:20.690
David S. Kong: You're a bird, or maybe you're not even a bird, but you're flying, and you can see down below, hundreds and hundreds of feet down, maybe miles down below, just the spots of…

1351
01:39:21.100 --> 01:39:22.979
David S. Kong: Houses and buildings.

1352
01:39:23.150 --> 01:39:24.940
David S. Kong: And it just goes on and on like that.

1353
01:39:25.070 --> 01:39:28.240
David S. Kong: And… I'll never have another one.

1354
01:39:28.890 --> 01:39:32.900
David S. Kong: But… The one was pretty good.

1355
01:39:33.830 --> 01:39:36.149
David S. Kong: And I like that I can go back and visit parts of it.

1356
01:39:43.300 --> 01:39:46.639
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I suspect sometimes that the lord of this house, too.

1357
01:39:51.710 --> 01:39:56.370
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Lives always with a sense of having lost something that won't come back again.

1358
01:39:56.650 --> 01:40:00.490
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Not just that won't come back again, that can't ever come back again.

1359
01:40:02.090 --> 01:40:03.309
David S. Kong: Wait, say that last part again?

1360
01:40:04.670 --> 01:40:06.500
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): That the Lord of this house.

1361
01:40:07.080 --> 01:40:12.599
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Lives having lost something like you that he cannot ever recover once again.

1362
01:40:12.600 --> 01:40:13.570
David S. Kong: Mmm…

1363
01:40:14.320 --> 01:40:22.479
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): But I don't hear you describing it as… loss, or… grief, I hear…

1364
01:40:26.550 --> 01:40:28.300
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Acceptance of that change?

1365
01:40:29.950 --> 01:40:33.060
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Totally.

1366
01:40:34.620 --> 01:40:37.220
David S. Kong: No regrets, no remorse. Onwards.

1367
01:40:38.410 --> 01:40:39.620
Audio shared by David S. Kong: It is what it is.

1368
01:40:45.710 --> 01:40:49.759
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Kit, I don't want to cut you off if you've got one lined up, but I'm also happy to move us in.

1369
01:40:50.740 --> 01:40:51.609
Audio shared by David S. Kong: But alright.

1370
01:40:51.880 --> 01:40:53.799
Audio shared by David S. Kong: I would… if, if we…

1371
01:40:53.800 --> 01:40:57.170
Kate Sackton: Got flummoxed by the Elves Don't Dream. I had something to say to…

1372
01:40:57.170 --> 01:40:58.120
Audio shared by David S. Kong: You know, full.

1373
01:40:58.120 --> 01:41:02.260
Kate Sackton: third one, so we need it as needed, but I'm fine.

1374
01:41:03.790 --> 01:41:07.970
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): They gesture for you to step through the gate.

1375
01:41:10.820 --> 01:41:11.330
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Stop.

1376
01:41:11.330 --> 01:41:12.449
Audio shared by David S. Kong: flipping through.

1377
01:41:13.820 --> 01:41:18.329
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You see the long… actually, Tim, will you put on the next, background for us?

1378
01:41:18.890 --> 01:41:28.020
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You see the long, sloping lawn that leads from the river's edge up to the patios and open doors of a bright and handsome house.

1379
01:41:28.390 --> 01:41:36.429
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You see string lights strung in globes going down the hill as the ground falls away ahead of you.

1380
01:41:38.040 --> 01:41:42.489
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You see, groups 1s and twos and 4s and fives.

1381
01:41:46.420 --> 01:41:50.110
Audio shared by David S. Kong: You see the signs of a party ending?

1382
01:41:51.220 --> 01:41:57.649
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The lighting is strange in the house, uneven. Some rooms brightly lit, and some less so.

