02:24:17.360 --> 02:24:22.770
Kate Sackton: We are… Traveling together, Edric and I, and we have some stories.

1956
02:24:25.960 --> 02:24:27.129
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Where are you from?

1957
02:24:30.780 --> 02:24:32.060
Kate Sackton: We're from Toland.

1958
02:24:32.850 --> 02:24:34.620
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Do you have a home there?

1959
02:24:36.380 --> 02:24:37.280
Kate Sackton: I do.

1960
02:24:43.050 --> 02:24:47.580
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Allow me to stay in your home for a month and a day the next time I'm in Tolin.

1961
02:24:49.120 --> 02:24:49.790
Kate Sackton: Hmm.

1962
02:24:52.760 --> 02:24:55.540
Kate Sackton: Is there a significance of that timing among your people?

1963
02:24:55.940 --> 02:24:58.170
Kate Sackton: I've not met anyone like you before.

1964
02:24:59.750 --> 02:25:01.870
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): were Southerners, mostly.

1965
02:25:05.580 --> 02:25:10.910
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): No, it's mostly that I think I have about a month's worth of… Sights to see.

1966
02:25:11.780 --> 02:25:13.520
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): It's a big city, after all.

1967
02:25:18.410 --> 02:25:20.339
Kate Sackton: Does it matter that I don't own the home?

1968
02:25:28.530 --> 02:25:32.079
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Do you have a room of your own, undisturbed?

1969
02:25:33.060 --> 02:25:33.660
Kate Sackton: Yes.

1970
02:25:35.350 --> 02:25:37.430
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Then I'll have that for a month and a day.

1971
02:25:41.030 --> 02:25:43.440
Kate Sackton: Well, it's unlikely that my parents would object.

1972
02:25:47.350 --> 02:25:48.310
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Very good.

1973
02:25:52.110 --> 02:25:54.460
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): He reaches out at Paul, which is…

1974
02:25:55.320 --> 02:25:59.980
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I don't know, easily 4 or 5 times the size of your own hand to shake.

1975
02:26:06.020 --> 02:26:06.679
Kate Sackton: Edric, can you.

1976
02:26:06.680 --> 02:26:09.340
Mike: Kind of looking at you like, are you sure you want to do this?

1977
02:26:09.790 --> 02:26:15.149
Kate Sackton: I don't. I'm looking at… I'm asking you a question to distract from shaking this creature's hand.

1978
02:26:15.290 --> 02:26:17.220
Kate Sackton: Edric, have you met my parents?

1979
02:26:19.580 --> 02:26:21.590
Mike: I… yes?

1980
02:26:28.560 --> 02:26:30.459
Kate Sackton: You would want me to ask their permission?

1981
02:26:33.270 --> 02:26:36.339
Kate Sackton: Because I'm sorry, sir, I'm beginning to wonder if I ought to.

1982
02:26:36.680 --> 02:26:37.220
Kate Sackton: And they're not…

1983
02:26:37.390 --> 02:26:40.919
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): It would be easier if I arrived as a man.

1984
02:26:41.030 --> 02:26:42.539
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I would be happy to.

1985
02:26:47.460 --> 02:26:49.430
Kate Sackton: I mean, some of my best friends look…

1986
02:26:50.620 --> 02:26:57.339
Kate Sackton: Like, all na… all number of animals, and… well, not that's a wrong way of saying that, I've got to say that a different way.

1987
02:27:00.620 --> 02:27:02.850
Kate Sackton: Not everybody knows theirs is a van.

1988
02:27:03.300 --> 02:27:07.280
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): He occupies himself with, or,

1989
02:27:08.170 --> 02:27:14.889
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Has the affectation, at least, of fiddling with his pipe and sprinkling him in fresh tobacco from a pouch on his belt.

1990
02:27:15.800 --> 02:27:19.259
Kate Sackton: Oh, that's very thoughtful of you, to cover my blunders.

1991
02:27:25.030 --> 02:27:28.830
Kate Sackton: I don't think it would matter what you… I don't think it matters what you look like, sir.

1992
02:27:30.490 --> 02:27:32.420
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Well, that's very open-minded of you.

1993
02:27:36.140 --> 02:27:44.320
Kate Sackton: Is there anything other than a stay in my parents' home, which I cannot grant, that I could offer you for a hint at your discovery?

1994
02:27:52.960 --> 02:27:54.950
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Do you have any keys on your personnel?

1995
02:28:02.230 --> 02:28:03.649
Kate Sackton: Don't have any keys.

1996
02:28:06.530 --> 02:28:11.829
Kate Sackton: But my friend could… probably has one. He tends to have interesting things in his pockets.

1997
02:28:13.780 --> 02:28:15.169
Kate Sackton: I haven't seen Taric in a while.

1998
02:28:18.640 --> 02:28:20.860
Tim Sackton: Eric has gotta have a key on him.

1999
02:28:21.660 --> 02:28:22.790
Kate Sackton: Yeah, that's what I think.

2000
02:28:24.180 --> 02:28:25.010
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Very good.

2001
02:28:25.010 --> 02:28:25.979
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I'll do it in exchange.

2002
02:28:25.980 --> 02:28:27.560
Kate Sackton: Where we don't know where it is.

2003
02:28:29.700 --> 02:28:30.240
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Exactly.

2004
02:28:32.770 --> 02:28:33.730
Kate Sackton: Speak of the devil.

2005
02:28:40.190 --> 02:28:40.800
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Eric, how you doing?

2006
02:28:40.800 --> 02:28:43.740
Kate Sackton: in here with a key in his pocket, that would be perfect.

2007
02:28:50.510 --> 02:28:51.679
Eric Rosenbaum: That was no fun.

2008
02:28:52.100 --> 02:28:53.199
Eric Rosenbaum: Oh, I missed that.

2009
02:28:54.210 --> 02:28:54.910
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Oops.

2010
02:28:55.660 --> 02:29:01.419
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Real-life use of stealth, though, to get out of the room once they're finally asleep, which…

2011
02:29:02.230 --> 02:29:03.469
Eric Rosenbaum: Come on, outside sides.

2012
02:29:07.950 --> 02:29:09.429
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Come into the party.

2013
02:29:10.550 --> 02:29:16.139
Audio shared by David S. Kong: talked to a couple of extremely drunk halflings that may have been in the Feywild for…

2014
02:29:16.480 --> 02:29:18.330
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Hundreds upon hundreds of years.

2015
02:29:18.760 --> 02:29:27.750
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And… Iveen and Edric are in a…

2016
02:29:27.880 --> 02:29:33.940
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): back porch of the house, where they've stumbled into a rakshasa, a giant.

2017
02:29:34.360 --> 02:29:38.230
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Tiger person, smoking a pipe.

2018
02:29:38.580 --> 02:29:46.360
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Who's told them that he has figured out the story of the Lord of the party.

2019
02:29:46.540 --> 02:29:59.580
Audio shared by David S. Kong: the lord of the Manor here, and is willing to trade it. First, he tried to get a stay in Kate's, excuse me, in Iveen's parents' home for a month and a day, but she seemed to decide that was a bad idea, and now he's asking for,

2020
02:29:59.580 --> 02:30:00.170
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): the key.

2021
02:30:02.600 --> 02:30:09.370
Tim Sackton: So we're thinking Taric might wander by with a key at this precise moment, since surely Taric has keys in his pocket.

2022
02:30:09.910 --> 02:30:14.260
Kate Sackton: Preferably keys you don't care about, that belong to somebody else we don't even care.

2023
02:30:14.660 --> 02:30:15.300
Kate Sackton: What they're talking about.

2024
02:30:15.300 --> 02:30:16.880
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Eric would never have keys.

2025
02:30:17.100 --> 02:30:17.920
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Dude, it's…

2026
02:30:17.920 --> 02:30:19.130
Tim Sackton: own stuff.

2027
02:30:19.910 --> 02:30:21.210
Kate Sackton: Exactly.

2028
02:30:23.500 --> 02:30:28.300
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Yeah, of course, Taric has a set of keys.

2029
02:30:39.030 --> 02:30:39.960
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The…

2030
02:30:44.410 --> 02:30:44.800
Kate Sackton: Okay?

2031
02:30:44.800 --> 02:30:47.609
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Tarek, as you…

2032
02:30:47.610 --> 02:30:52.790
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Cross through one of the rooms in the manor, he catches your eye and waves you over with an immense.

2033
02:30:53.060 --> 02:30:57.800
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Tiger paw, says, come, come, we were just, speaking of you, I believe.

2034
02:30:58.210 --> 02:31:01.319
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Your friends have, made a deal in your name.

2035
02:31:02.410 --> 02:31:04.629
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You have keys on you.

2036
02:31:06.540 --> 02:31:08.480
Eric Rosenbaum: I have keys of many kinds.

2037
02:31:08.650 --> 02:31:10.580
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Mmm. Very good.

2038
02:31:12.140 --> 02:31:13.800
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Allow me to share insight.

2039
02:31:14.300 --> 02:31:15.609
Audio shared by David S. Kong: keys of wisdom.

2040
02:31:15.800 --> 02:31:17.500
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Keys to cryptograms.

2041
02:31:18.030 --> 02:31:18.750
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Choose three.

2042
02:31:21.110 --> 02:31:22.559
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I need keys for doors.

2043
02:31:24.200 --> 02:31:24.980
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Mmm.

2044
02:31:26.590 --> 02:31:32.280
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Well… And Tarek rummages around in his…

2045
02:31:35.480 --> 02:31:38.229
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Garments for a minute, patting his pockets.

2046
02:31:43.410 --> 02:31:44.579
Audio shared by David S. Kong: I.

2047
02:31:44.580 --> 02:31:45.600
Eric Rosenbaum: Why, yes.

2048
02:31:46.960 --> 02:31:48.680
Eric Rosenbaum: He's.

2049
02:31:52.300 --> 02:31:53.560
Eric Rosenbaum: Keys to the museum.

2050
02:31:55.740 --> 02:31:56.970
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Hmm…

2051
02:31:57.410 --> 02:31:58.380
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Very good.

2052
02:32:00.380 --> 02:32:07.559
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): he… Brings his whole face over very close, and takes out a pair of spectacles and puts them on.

2053
02:32:07.710 --> 02:32:10.950
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And looks long and deep at each of the keys.

2054
02:32:11.520 --> 02:32:12.890
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And.

2055
02:32:13.360 --> 02:32:19.110
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Picks 3 with… No discernible reason that you can tell from any of them.

2056
02:32:19.220 --> 02:32:24.520
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And slips them into his waistcoat pocket. Takes off his spectacles.

2057
02:32:25.150 --> 02:32:26.820
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Sits back in his chair.

2058
02:32:27.310 --> 02:32:31.370
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Takes a long puff on the pipe that he's smoking from.

2059
02:32:31.700 --> 02:32:40.880
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): It says, Mmm… this is… This is a delicious story.

2060
02:32:41.010 --> 02:32:43.030
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): A delicious story.

2061
02:32:44.590 --> 02:32:54.029
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I came to the Twilight Kingdom. To the dozen dozen houses…

2062
02:32:56.040 --> 02:33:00.180
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Because there are certain things you can only find in Twilight.

2063
02:33:01.450 --> 02:33:06.049
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Things that have been lost and can't be found again?

2064
02:33:07.000 --> 02:33:11.860
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): places that can never be returned to, and I…

2065
02:33:11.990 --> 02:33:17.960
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): In my younger days, got obsessive about that sort of a time, that moment.

2066
02:33:20.220 --> 02:33:27.560
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The moment all of the past has ended, but before the future's begun yet, the moment when things are beginning…

2067
02:33:28.840 --> 02:33:30.500
Audio shared by David S. Kong: But haven't yet begun.

2068
02:33:31.470 --> 02:33:35.829
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I got, you might say, obsessive over this, and decided…

2069
02:33:36.850 --> 02:33:40.660
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I would spend a day traveling the Twilight Kingdoms.

2070
02:33:42.910 --> 02:33:46.410
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I pieced this together from the various guests.

2071
02:33:46.800 --> 02:33:49.620
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Most of the ones who are here now

2072
02:33:50.150 --> 02:33:53.860
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Arrived at the party when it was just beginning.

2073
02:33:54.110 --> 02:33:58.740
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Or arrived here, too, when it was in full swing, before…

2074
02:33:59.240 --> 02:34:00.280
Audio shared by David S. Kong: This.

2075
02:34:00.430 --> 02:34:02.459
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And he gestures to the sort of…

2076
02:34:02.460 --> 02:34:05.680
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Ineffitable feeling of everything coming apart.

2077
02:34:11.880 --> 02:34:13.600
Audio shared by David S. Kong: The height of the party.

2078
02:34:14.870 --> 02:34:17.609
Audio shared by David S. Kong: The neighbors. The neighbors.

2079
02:34:17.870 --> 02:34:22.400
Audio shared by David S. Kong: who lived… One house down the street, at the height of the party.

2080
02:34:23.550 --> 02:34:28.219
Audio shared by David S. Kong: came to the lord of this house, whose name was Lord Revel.

2081
02:34:28.370 --> 02:34:29.740
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Revel Beginning.

2082
02:34:33.020 --> 02:34:35.059
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And they wanted from him

2083
02:34:35.730 --> 02:34:41.719
Audio shared by David S. Kong: sort of a bargain. They wanted an agreement. They wanted him to do something for them.

2084
02:34:43.410 --> 02:34:49.610
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): That any mortal who visited the party Sooner or later.

2085
02:34:49.750 --> 02:34:54.869
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Would be sent through the front door of their house, just up the road.

2086
02:34:59.170 --> 02:35:04.470
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): It's difficult to persuade a Feylord of anything at all.

2087
02:35:06.680 --> 02:35:08.110
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): More difficult still.

2088
02:35:08.880 --> 02:35:13.829
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): To persuade him to do harm to his guests.

2089
02:35:14.380 --> 02:35:19.459
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Which surely breaks one of the most basic rules of the dozen dozen houses.

2090
02:35:21.730 --> 02:35:25.649
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): They gave him first things they found precious.

2091
02:35:26.210 --> 02:35:31.059
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The sort of things humans found precious. Books from their library.

2092
02:35:31.780 --> 02:35:35.919
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): A bird that could speak every language?

2093
02:35:36.080 --> 02:35:41.800
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): A map of the stars that twilight had not yet revealed overhead.

2094
02:35:42.900 --> 02:35:44.480
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): But for Lord Revel.

2095
02:35:44.800 --> 02:35:55.040
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): This was of no consequence. Every guest brings gifts to his party. Or, he says, chuckling, looking over you, or bribes the guards.

2096
02:35:57.730 --> 02:36:01.669
Audio shared by David S. Kong: So next… Thinking that he wanted.

2097
02:36:01.670 --> 02:36:14.959
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Inspiration for his revelry, they gave him stories of human revelry, of fireworks like rainbows, above a city made entirely of towers and pyramids.

2098
02:36:15.880 --> 02:36:17.280
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): of does.

2099
02:36:19.290 --> 02:36:20.530
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): They told him…

2100
02:36:21.440 --> 02:36:32.130
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): About the 10 days of celebration that followed the Emperor's coronation, and everything they saw there, performers, from the endless ocean and beyond it.

2101
02:36:34.810 --> 02:36:36.690
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): They told him stories.

2102
02:36:37.510 --> 02:36:43.180
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Of how the bonfires burned through the longest night on the floating cities.

2103
02:36:43.650 --> 02:36:55.980
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Far beyond the edge of the endless ocean. But none of these stories of Revel were of any value. Not to Lord Revel, who was himself Revelry.

2104
02:36:57.090 --> 02:37:13.989
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And the dozen dozen houses of the Twilight Kingdom have celebrations for which there is no word in mortal tongue to describe them. So in desperation, drawing on some book of lore they must have found, they challenged him instead to a game, to a contest.

2105
02:37:14.150 --> 02:37:17.519
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): A game of poetry. A game of naming.

2106
02:37:18.920 --> 02:37:24.720
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Whoever could most beautifully name Lord Revel's estate.

2107
02:37:26.260 --> 02:37:29.570
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Well, then they could ask one favor of the other.

2108
02:37:32.380 --> 02:37:33.600
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Lord Revel went.

2109
02:37:33.600 --> 02:37:34.630
Audio shared by David S. Kong: First.

2110
02:37:35.920 --> 02:37:36.730
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And…

2111
02:37:36.830 --> 02:37:38.619
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Spoke the name?

2112
02:37:40.730 --> 02:37:43.860
Audio shared by David S. Kong: As it had been all evening long.

2113
02:37:45.290 --> 02:37:47.160
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Wide lungs.

2114
02:37:47.260 --> 02:37:49.309
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Spread down easy.

2115
02:37:49.600 --> 02:37:55.860
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Hanging lanterns welcome you. A party begins, Lord Revel. Beginning.

2116
02:37:59.190 --> 02:38:03.210
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): But this wizard… Guessed correctly.

2117
02:38:04.110 --> 02:38:23.910
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): That Revel was trapped inside of his own story. Trapped, in fact, by his own immortality, trapped by the frozenness in time, unable to imagine that his story had any other moment, or could have any other moment in it except for the present.

2118
02:38:26.080 --> 02:38:27.270
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): This wizard.

2119
02:38:28.060 --> 02:38:31.550
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Guessed correctly that Revel could not imagine…

2120
02:38:31.700 --> 02:38:41.979
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): That the wine would spill and run out, that the guests would slowly drift away, and the players on the patio grow tired.

2121
02:38:43.800 --> 02:38:47.029
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): So the wizard did not speak the name.

2122
02:38:47.610 --> 02:38:49.839
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Of this house as it is.

2123
02:38:50.870 --> 02:38:55.079
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): He spoke the name of this house as it would become.

2124
02:38:55.550 --> 02:39:00.830
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Saying, Wide lawns gone askew.

2125
02:39:01.540 --> 02:39:08.170
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Hanging lanterns flicker low. A party ending. Lord, endless ending.

2126
02:39:10.640 --> 02:39:13.689
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And in that act of naming.

2127
02:39:15.760 --> 02:39:22.809
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): With whatever power and lore this human had at his disposal in that act of naming.

2128
02:39:23.550 --> 02:39:25.479
Audio shared by David S. Kong: The lord of the house looked up.

2129
02:39:26.090 --> 02:39:31.250
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And saw, indeed, it was so. Empty glasses sat on every surface.

2130
02:39:31.870 --> 02:39:34.720
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Already the candles were burning out.

2131
02:39:35.640 --> 02:39:45.110
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And a small boat was already in the water, the rowers calling out farewell, and the chill of evening entered the air for the first time.

2132
02:39:47.000 --> 02:39:49.669
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And that is the moment it has been.

2133
02:39:50.310 --> 02:39:51.790
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Ever since.

2134
02:39:53.260 --> 02:39:58.220
Audio shared by David S. Kong: From time to time, The grandfather clock chimes.

2135
02:39:58.760 --> 02:39:59.940
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And Lord.

2136
02:39:59.990 --> 02:40:06.690
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Endlessly ending sends another mortal guest down the road, but whether that's been once…

2137
02:40:06.800 --> 02:40:09.240
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Or a hundred times.

2138
02:40:10.020 --> 02:40:11.220
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Who can say?

2139
02:40:13.360 --> 02:40:22.170
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And at the edges of his vision, just beyond where he can see, Despair.

2140
02:40:22.170 --> 02:40:28.660
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): hovers around the Lord now, not of reveled beginning, but of an endless ending.

2141
02:40:29.340 --> 02:40:31.989
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And soon he will be alone.

2142
02:40:32.510 --> 02:40:35.399
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): In an empty, messy house.

2143
02:40:35.930 --> 02:40:36.970
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The best.

2144
02:40:37.590 --> 02:40:38.889
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Well behind him.

2145
02:40:41.750 --> 02:40:43.349
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): That's our host.

2146
02:40:44.600 --> 02:40:46.260
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And that's enough story.

2147
02:40:46.280 --> 02:40:50.750
Audio shared by David S. Kong: For me, I had just… one more…

2148
02:40:50.800 --> 02:40:52.159
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Bull to smoke.

2149
02:40:53.060 --> 02:40:56.410
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And then I go on to the next of the kingdoms.

2150
02:40:56.940 --> 02:40:58.990
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The next of the houses, I should say.

